    {
        "content": "<p>Hey everyone,</p>\n<p>I am currently experimenting with the delaboration of Lean4. My goal is to convert a syntax into another type that still retains part of the plain syntax. However, when I try to match the syntax and return it in the desired type, I get an error. I suspect this is because I can't \"lift\" the syntax, but I can't use the ← symbol outside of a monad.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">declare_syntax_cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">testSyntax</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">syntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"⸨+⸩\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">testSyntax</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">syntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"⸨-⸩\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">testSyntax</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">testFunction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TSyntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`term</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">TSyntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`testSyntax</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">testSyntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">n1</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⸨+⸩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">n2</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cons</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">testSyntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">n1</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⸨+⸩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">n2</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">nil</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">testSyntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">n1</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⸨-⸩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">n2</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cons</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">testSyntax</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">n1</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⸨-⸩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">n2</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">num</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">nil</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">nil</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Does anyone know how to return this TSyntax or suggest a monad that I can use?</p>",
